.SH "NAME"
\fBredis_log_pipe\fR \- Pipe log lines from STDIN to redis
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
redis_log_pipe takes log lines on STDIN and pipes them to redis \fIhttp://redis\.io\fR\.
.
.P
It connects to a redis server located at \fIREDIS_LOG_HOST\fR (default: 127\.0\.0\.1:6379)\.
.
.P
It LPUSHes \fIhttp://redis\.io/commands/lpush\fR them to a LIST \fIhttp://redis\.io/topics/data\-types\fR called "\fIkey\fR"\. It trims the list to \fIRETENTION\fR (default: 250) using LTRIM \fIhttp://redis\.io/commands/ltrim\fR\. It also PUBLISHes \fIhttp://redis\.io/commands/publish\fR them to a channel \fIhttp://redis\.io/topics/pubsub\fR called "channels\.\fIkey\fR"\.
.
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.
.TP
key
The redis key to use for the list\.
.
.IP
By convention, the log will be published to a channel named channels\.\fIkey\fR as well\.
.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES"
.
.TP
REDIS_LOG_HOST
[\fIpassword\fR@]\fIhost\fR:\fIport\fR
.
.IP
The redis password, host and port\. Password optional\.
.
.br
Default: 127\.0\.0\.1:6379
.
.TP
RETENTION
Number of log lines to retain in the list for tailing\.
.
.br
Default: 250
.
